Blender (pros)
- Free and open source
- ideal for beginners
- Strong on MODELLING and UV TOOLS than Maya
- many tutorials available for help
- BETTER AT RENDERING

Blender (cons)
- can be overwhelming due to diverse tool set
- good for indie projects not industry


Maya (pros)
- powerful for animations
- BETTER FOR DETAILED ANIMATION WORK FLOW
- industrial standard for making 3D videos
- rigging is much better hence BETTER ANIMATION and VISUAL EFFECTS
- cheaper version Maya LT available with few features, $265/year

Maya (cons)
- Expensive, $1620/year
- can be challenging to learn
- rendering animation for the first time can be challenging
